Microsoft Clarity
clarity
Description
Description
We use the analytics tool Microsoft Clarity from Microsoft Corporation (Microsoft Corporation, One
Microsoft Way, Redmond, WA 98052-6399, USA; “Microsoft”) to record how you use and interact with
our website. This involves the use of behavioural metrics, heatmaps and the analysis of repeat
sessions with the aim of improving our products and services. Website usage data is recorded using
cookies from first and third-party providers as well as other tracking technologies to establish the
popularity of products, services and online activities. We also use this information to optimise the
website for security purposes and to combat fraud.
The legal basis is Art. 6 Par. 1 Sentence 1 Letter a GDPR. Please see the Microsoft Privacy
Statement https://privacy.microsoft.com/en-gb/privacystatement for more information on how Microsoft
collects and uses your data.
